    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>Java array reflection is for cases where you don't have an instance of the Class available to do \"instanceof\" on.  For example, if you're writing some sort of injection framework, that injects values into a new instance of a class, such as JPA does, then you need to use the isArray() functionality.</p>\n\n<p>I blogged about this earlier in December.\n<a href=\"http://blog.adamsbros.org/2010/12/08/java-array-reflection/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://blog.adamsbros.org/2010/12/08/java-array-reflection/</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 111563,
        "reputation" : 16084,
        "user_id" : 294657,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 85,
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c858688cffaffffb2dfabae6bc89ba7e?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "kaqqao",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/294657/kaqqao"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1512738408,
      "post_id" : 12873642,
      "comment_id" : 82389997,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "This makes no sense. <code>isArray</code> is a method of <code>Class</code>, not <code>Type</code>, so of course <code>GenericArrayTypeImpl</code> doesn&#39;t have that method. And <code>getClass</code> can never return a non-<code>Class</code> <code>Type</code>, so you (or Groovy??) must have done something wrong to get this, like assuming every <code>Type</code> is a <code>Class</code>."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1934954,
      "reputation" : 1723,
      "user_id" : 1743446,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/52d0b036ccbae9bdf920042f3a3b176f?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "dturanski",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1743446/dturanski"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1350135854,
    "last_edit_date" : 1350135854,
    "creation_date" : 1350135577,
    "answer_id" : 12873642,
    "question_id" : 219881,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I recently ran into an issue upgrading a Groovy application from JDK 5 to JDK 6.  Using <code>isArray()</code> failed in JDK6:</p>\n\n<pre><code>MissingMethodException:\nNo signature of sun.reflect.generics.reflectiveObjects.GenericArrayTypeImpl.isArray() ...\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Changing to <code>instanceof Object[]</code> fixed this. </p>\n"
  } ],
